rComments: He devotes a lot time in office hours, however, I wouldn't think his research is something that I would like to call research: simple assumptions, nothing but adding up numbers and ignore women's role totally.  because of that. This prof is teaching one concept for the whole semester, so the classes get a bit repetetive beginning from the second lecture. It's a very easy course, but beware of the papers - he grades them a bit unpredictable and unfair. If your goal to get an "A", this class may become a big headache..
demanding but very helpful and his lectures are clear to understand and interesting
One of the best I ever had !

One of the U of T Super-Stars. Best selling author. Well packaged, friendly lecturer. Easy material, but the pick-your-own-topic project demands a lot of work and good applied econometrics. Very available and helpful in his office. A must!
A really good course. Good prof, too. Impressive that he still teaches after writing such a bestseller.
